      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why J Words Pack a Scoring Punch</h2>
      <p>J is the overlooked premium tile in Scrabble. At 8 points — the same value as X — J flies under the radar because players fixate on Q and Z. But J has a critical advantage: it combines with other premium tiles more readily than any other letter. JACUZZI pairs J with Z for 34 points. JOCKEY uses J+K+Y for 22 points. JINX pairs J+X for 18 points in just 4 letters. JIGSAW combines J+W for 17 points.</p>
      <p>J also has a solid two-letter word: JO scores 9 points and works in tight board positions. This means J, like X, is never completely stuck — you always have at least a 9-point play available. The J-prefix is productive too: JOLLY, JOCKEY, JEWELRY, JIGSAW, and JINX all start with J and use common rack letters. Combined with its partnerships with other high-value tiles, J is arguably the most efficient premium tile in the game when you measure scoring potential against playability. JACUZZI (34 pts) is one of the highest-scoring words achievable in regular play.</p>

